All points referred to are indicated on the plan and are marked on the ground as follows: points 4 to 11 by Old P.S. and the rest by P.S. Cyl. Conc. Mons. 15 x 60 cms.; bearings true; date of original survey, August 1906 – July 1907, and that of the subdivision survey, executed by Renato H. Cabigon, Geodetic Engineer, on Sept. 25, 1977.

